title: Application SOX Controls - SCOM Group scope

source.script:
[System.Collections.ArrayList]$myList = @()

$ServerInstance= 'SQL_DB_Instance_For_Your_Application'
$DatabaseName='SalesForce'
 
$SQLQuery = "
SELECT
       T1.USER_            AS USER_
     , T2.NAME             AS ROLENAME     
     , CASE T4.ENABLE WHEN 0 THEN 'Disabled' WHEN 1 THEN 'Enabled' END           AS AccountEnable
     , T4.NETWORKALIAS     AS NETWORKALIAS
     , T4.NETWORKDOMAIN    AS NETWORKDOMAIN
     , T4.NAME             AS USERNAME
FROM
       SECURITYUSERROLE T1
       CROSS JOIN
              SECURITYROLE_INLINEFUNC(N'en_us') T2
       LEFT OUTER JOIN
              OMUSERROLEORGANIZATION T3
              ON
                     (
                            (
                                   T1.SECURITYROLE=T3.SECURITYROLE
                                   AND
                                   (
                                          T1.PARTITION = T3.PARTITION
                                   )
                            )
                            AND
                            (
                                   T1.USER_=T3.USER_
                                   AND
                                   (
                                          T1.PARTITION = T3.PARTITION
                                   )
                            )
                     )
       CROSS JOIN
              USERINFO T4
       LEFT OUTER JOIN
              DIRPARTYTABLE T5
              ON
                     (
                            T3.OMINTERNALORGANIZATION=T5.RECID
                            AND
                            (
                                   T3.PARTITION = T5.PARTITION
                            )
                     )
WHERE
       (
              T1.SECURITYROLE=T2.RECID
       )
       AND
       (
              T1.USER_=T4.ID
              AND
              (
                     T1.PARTITION = T4.PARTITION
              )
       )
       AND
       (
            T2.NAME = 'System administrator'
       )
"  
  
  #Create a Connection to SQL Server
$sqlConn = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection
$sqlConn.ConnectionString = "Server=$ServerInstance;Integrated Security=true;Initial Catalog=$DatabaseName"
$sqlConn.Open()

#Get our command pipeline set up
$sqlcmd = $sqlConn.CreateCommand()
$sqlcmd = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
$sqlcmd.Connection = $sqlConn
$sqlcmd.CommandText = $SQLQuery

#Create the Data Adapter
$adp = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlDataAdapter $sqlcmd

#Create and fill the DataSet
$ds = New-Object System.Data.DataSet
$t = $adp.Fill($ds)

#Save our SQL Results
$SQLResults = $ds.Tables[0].Rows
$Results = @($SQLResults)

 ForEach ($Result in $Results ) { 
        $myobj = New-Object PSObject
        	$Username=$Result.UserName
       		       
            Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName Username -NotePropertyValue $Username    
            Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName Domain -NotePropertyValue $Result.NETWORKDOMAIN    
            Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName UserID -NotePropertyValue $Result.USER_ 
			 Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName Account -NotePropertyValue $ADUsername 
            
   
               if ($TeamADmin.SamAccountName.Contains($Username) -Or $AuthorizedAppsAdmins -like $ADUsername){
                  Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Healthy' 
                }elseif($Username.Contains('NonProd') -Or $TeamDEV.SamAccountName -like $Username)
                {
                   Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Critical' 
                } 
                elseif($ERPTeamERP.SamAccountName -like $Username){
                   Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Warning' 
                }else{
                	Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Warning' 
                } 
				Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName AccountEnable -NotePropertyValue   $Result.AccountEnable
          
            [void]$mylist.add($myobj)
           
        }
    
 
$myList

[System.Collections.ArrayList]$myList = @()

$ServerInstance= 'SQL_DB_Instance_For_Your_Application'
$DatabaseName='master'
 
$SQLQuery = "
SELECT   name,type_desc,is_disabled
FROM     sys.server_principals
WHERE    IS_SRVROLEMEMBER ('sysadmin',name) = 1
"  
  
  #Create a Connection to SQL Server
$sqlConn = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection
$sqlConn.ConnectionString = "Server=$ServerInstance;Integrated Security=true;Initial Catalog=$DatabaseName"
$sqlConn.Open()
 
#Get our command pipeline set up
$sqlcmd = $sqlConn.CreateCommand()
$sqlcmd = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlCommand
$sqlcmd.Connection = $sqlConn
$sqlcmd.CommandText = $SQLQuery

#Create the Data Adapter
$adp = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlDataAdapter $sqlcmd

#Create and fill the DataSet
$ds = New-Object System.Data.DataSet
$t = $adp.Fill($ds)

#Save our SQL Results
$SQLResults = $ds.Tables[0].Rows
$Results = @($SQLResults)

 ForEach ($Result in $Results ) { 
        $myobj = New-Object PSObject
        	$Username=$Result.name
       		
       
            Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName Username -NotePropertyValue $Username    
            Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName AccountType -NotePropertyValue $Result.type_desc    
            Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName Enabled -NotePropertyValue $Result.is_disabled 
			
            #Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Healthy' 

          	 if ($AuthorizedDBAdmins -like $Username){
                  Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Healthy' 
                }elseif($Username.Contains('NonProd') -Or $DEV.SamAccountName -like $Username)
                {
                   Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Critical' 
                } 
                elseif($TeamADmin.SamAccountName -like $Username){
                   Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Warning' 
                }else{
                	Add-Member -InputObject $myobj -NotePropertyName state -NotePropertyValue  'Warning' 
                } 
                
            [void]$mylist.add($myobj)
          
        }  
$myList
